alt + enter : PyCharm can guess your intention

ctrl + shift + A : find action

shift + shift : find action

ctrl + w : to select the word under the caret

ctrl + w + w : to select the whole string

ctrl + w + w + w : to include quotes in the selection

ctrl + w + w + w + w : to select the whole block of code

ctrl + / : to comment a line or multiple lines

ctrl + d : to duplicate a line or multiple lines

ctrl + y : to delete current line

alt + shift + down | up : to rearranging lines

ctrl + shift + down | up : to rearranging methods

ctrl + minus : to to collapse a piece of code

ctrl + equals | plus : to expand a code region

ctrl + shift + minus : to collapse all regions in the file

ctrl + shift + equals | plus : to expand all available regions



